---
import BaseHead from '../components/BaseHead.astro';
import Header from '../components/Header.astro';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';
import { SITE_TITLE } from '../consts';

const lastUpdated = 'April 17, 2026';
---

<!doctype html>
<html lang="en">
	<head>
		<BaseHead
			title={`Terms of Service · ${SITE_TITLE}`}
			description="Terms of Service for Arca — the AI ops platform for small service businesses."
		/>
	</head>
	<body>
		<Header />
		<main class="legal">
			<div class="legal-inner">
				<div class="legal-eyebrow">Legal</div>
				<h1 class="legal-title">Terms of Service</h1>
				<p class="legal-updated">Last updated: {lastUpdated}</p>

				<p class="legal-lede">
					These terms govern your use of Arca. By signing up or using the platform, you agree
					to them. If you don't agree, don't use Arca. We wrote this in plain English so you
					can actually read it. Questions? Email <a href="mailto:legal@runarca.xyz">legal@runarca.xyz</a>.
				</p>

				<h2>1. Definitions</h2>
				<ul>
					<li><strong>"Arca"</strong> means the AI ops platform operated by Unbanked at runarca.xyz.</li>
					<li><strong>"Unbanked"</strong>, "we", "us", "our" means Unbanked, the company behind Arca.</li>
					<li><strong>"You"</strong> means the person or business using Arca.</li>
					<li><strong>"Workspace"</strong> means your isolated Arca environment — your tasks, data, and settings.</li>
					<li><strong>"Agent"</strong> means an AI assistant within Arca that carries out operations on your behalf.</li>
				</ul>

				<h2>2. Your account</h2>
				<p>
					You must be at least 16 years old to use Arca. You're responsible for keeping your
					credentials secure and for everything that happens under your account. If you believe
					someone has accessed your account without permission, email
					<a href="mailto:security@runarca.xyz">security@runarca.xyz</a> immediately.
				</p>
				<p>
					Each workspace is isolated. Your data does not mix with other workspaces. You can
					invite team members to your workspace, and you're responsible for their conduct.
				</p>

				<h2>3. What Arca does</h2>
				<p>
					Arca provides AI-powered operations assistance. You give instructions, and our
					agents execute them — managing tasks, sending messages, scheduling, reading email,
					working with files, and other operations work. Agents act on your behalf within the
					constraints you set.
				</p>
				<p>
					Arca is not a person. It can make mistakes. You should review important actions
					before they become irreversible. We are not liable for actions taken by agents
					that you authorized.
				</p>

				<h2>4. Third-party integrations</h2>
				<p>
					Arca can connect to third-party services you authorize, including Google Workspace
					(Gmail, Calendar, Drive, Sheets, Slides), Telegram, and others. When you connect
					a service:
				</p>
				<ul>
					<li>You grant Arca access to your data in that service only for the purposes you enabled.</li>
					<li>Arca stores OAuth tokens securely and never shares your credentials with third parties.</li>
					<li>You can revoke access at any time from your integrations settings or directly from the third party (e.g., <a href="https://myaccount.google.com/permissions">Google permissions</a>).</li>
					<li>Your use of third-party services through Arca is also governed by those services' terms.</li>
				</ul>

				<h2>5. Your data</h2>
				<p>
					You own your data. We don't sell it, we don't train public AI models on it, and we
					don't use it for anything you didn't ask for. You can export or delete your data at
					any time by emailing <a href="mailto:privacy@runarca.xyz">privacy@runarca.xyz</a>.
				</p>
				<p>
					When you delete your account, we remove your data within 90 days (except for
					information we're required to keep by law, like billing records).
				</p>

				<h2>6. Acceptable use</h2>
				<p>You agree not to:</p>
				<ul>
					<li>Use Arca for anything illegal.</li>
					<li>Attempt to compromise Arca's security or infrastructure.</li>
					<li>Use Arca to send spam, harassment, or malicious content.</li>
					<li>Reverse-engineer, decompile, or create competing products from Arca.</li>
					<li>Share your account credentials with unauthorized people.</li>
					<li>Use Arca to process data you don't have permission to process.</li>
				</ul>

				<h2>7. Service availability</h2>
				<p>
					We strive for high availability but don't guarantee uptime. Arca is provided
					"as is" and "as available." We may modify, suspend, or discontinue features with
					notice. Scheduled maintenance windows are communicated in advance when possible.
				</p>

				<h2>8. Pricing and billing</h2>
				<p>
					Current pricing is listed at <a href="https://runarca.xyz">runarca.xyz</a>. We
					may change prices with 30 days' notice. If you're on a paid plan, we'll bill your
					payment method on file. Refund requests are handled on a case-by-case basis — email
					<a href="mailto:billing@runarca.xyz">billing@runarca.xyz</a>.
				</p>

				<h2>9. Intellectual property</h2>
				<p>
					Your content remains yours. By using Arca, you grant us a limited license to
					process your content solely to provide the service. We don't claim ownership of
					anything you create through Arca.
				</p>
				<p>
					The Arca platform, branding, and underlying technology are owned by Unbanked.
					You may not use our trademarks or branding without written permission.
				</p>

				<h2>10. Limitation of liability</h2>
				<p>
					To the maximum extent permitted by law: Unbanked is not liable for indirect,
					incidental, special, or consequential damages arising from your use of Arca,
					including but not limited to loss of data, revenue, or business opportunities.
					Our total liability for any claim is limited to the amount you paid us in the
					12 months before the claim arose.
				</p>

				<h2>11. Indemnification</h2>
				<p>
					You agree to indemnify Unbanked against claims arising from your use of Arca,
					including your content, your instructions to agents, and your compliance (or
					non-compliance) with applicable laws.
				</p>

				<h2>12. Termination</h2>
				<p>
					You can stop using Arca and delete your account at any time. We may suspend or
					terminate your account if you violate these terms, with notice where feasible.
					Upon termination, your right to use Arca ends, and we'll delete your data per
					Section 5.
				</p>

				<h2>13. Disputes</h2>
				<p>
					These terms are governed by the laws of Ontario, Canada. Any disputes will be
					resolved in the courts of Ontario. Before filing a claim, you agree to try
					resolving the issue by emailing
					<a href="mailto:legal@runarca.xyz">legal@runarca.xyz</a> and giving us 30 days
					to respond.
				</p>

				<h2>14. Changes to these terms</h2>
				<p>
					We may update these terms from time to time. For material changes, we'll give
					you at least 30 days' notice by email or a notice on runarca.xyz. Continued use
					after the effective date means you accept the updated terms.
				</p>

				<h2>15. Contact</h2>
				<p>
					Questions about these terms? Email
					<a href="mailto:legal@runarca.xyz">legal@runarca.xyz</a>. For privacy-specific
					questions, see our <a href="/privacy/">Privacy Policy</a>.
				</p>
			</div>
		</main>
		<Footer />

		<style>
			.legal {
				max-width: 820px;
				margin: 0 auto;
				padding: 96px 24px 120px;
			}
			.legal-eyebrow {
				color: var(--amber);
				font-weight: 800;
				font-size: 0.8125rem;
				letter-spacing: 0.18em;
				text-transform: uppercase;
				margin-bottom: 14px;
			}
			.legal-title {
				font-family: 'Plus Jakarta Sans', sans-serif;
				font-size: clamp(2rem, 5vw, 3rem);
				font-weight: 800;
				color: var(--charcoal);
				letter-spacing: -0.025em;
				line-height: 1.1;
				margin: 0 0 12px;
			}
			.legal-updated {
				color: var(--soft-charcoal);
				font-size: 0.9375rem;
				margin: 0 0 32px;
			}
			.legal-lede {
				font-size: 1.125rem;
				line-height: 1.7;
				color: var(--charcoal);
				margin: 0 0 48px;
				padding: 20px 24px;
				background: rgba(244, 194, 75, 0.08);
				border-left: 3px solid var(--amber);
				border-radius: 4px;
			}
			.legal h2 {
				font-family: 'Plus Jakarta Sans', sans-serif;
				font-size: 1.5rem;
				font-weight: 700;
				color: var(--charcoal);
				letter-spacing: -0.015em;
				margin: 48px 0 16px;
			}
			.legal h3 {
				font-family: 'Plus Jakarta Sans', sans-serif;
				font-size: 1.125rem;
				font-weight: 700;
				color: var(--charcoal);
				margin: 28px 0 12px;
			}
			.legal p,
			.legal li {
				color: var(--soft-charcoal);
				font-size: 1rem;
				line-height: 1.7;
			}
			.legal p {
				margin: 0 0 16px;
			}
			.legal ul {
				margin: 0 0 20px;
				padding-left: 22px;
			}
			.legal li {
				margin-bottom: 10px;
			}
			.legal a {
				color: var(--charcoal);
				text-decoration: underline;
				text-decoration-thickness: 1px;
				text-underline-offset: 3px;
			}
			.legal a:hover {
				color: var(--amber);
			}
			.legal strong {
				color: var(--charcoal);
			}
		</style>
	</body>
</html>